			    STPJS 258</div>
  <p class="cont">their purpose. God has enabled me to keep out of their hands.<span class="footRef">1</span> I have warred a good warfare,<span class="footRef">2</span>
  insomuch as I have outgeneralled or whipped out all Bennett&rsquo;s corrupt host.</p>
  <p class="std">My feelings at the present time are that, inasmuch as the Lord Almighty has preserved me<span class="footRef">3</span> until
  today, He will continue to preserve me,<span class="footRef">4</span> by the united faith and prayers of the Saints,<span class="footRef">5</span> until I have
  fully accomplished my mission in this life, and so firmly established the dispensation of the fullness
  of the priesthood<span class="footRef">6</span> in the last days, that all the powers of earth and hell<span class="footRef">7</span> can never prevail against it.<span class="footRef">8</span></p>
  <p class="std">This constant persecution reminds me of the words of the Savior, when He said to the Pharisees,
  &ldquo;Go ye, and tell that fox, Behold, I cast out devils, and I do cures today and tomorrow, and the third
  day I shall be perfected.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">9</span> I suspect that my Heavenly Father has decreed that the Missourians shall
  not get me into their power;<span class="footRef">10</span> if they do, it will be because I do not keep out of their way.</p>
  <p class="std">I shall triumph over my enemies:<span class="footRef">11</span> I have begun to triumph over them at home, and I shall do
  it abroad. All those that rise up against me<span class="footRef">12</span> will surely feel the weight of their iniquity upon their
  own heads.<span class="footRef">13</span> Those that speak evil<span class="footRef">14</span> of me and the Saints are ignorant or abominable characters, and
  full of iniquity.<span class="footRef">15</span> All the fuss, and all the stir, and all the charges got up against me are like the
  jack-a-lantern, which cannot be found.</p>
  <div class="topic">No Man Without Fault</div>
  <p class="std">Although I do wrong, I do not the wrongs that I am charged with doing; the wrong that I do is
  through the frailty of human nature, like other men.<span class="footRef">16</span> No man lives without fault. Do you think that
  even Jesus, if He were here, would be without fault in your eyes? His enemies said all manner of evil
  against Him<span class="footRef">17</span>&mdash;they all watched for iniquity in Him.<span class="footRef">18</span> How easy it was for Jesus to call out all the
  iniquity of the hearts<span class="footRef">19</span> of those whom He was among!</p>
  <div class="topic">Most Injury Comes from Little Evils</div>
  <p class="std">The servants of the Lord<span class="footRef">20</span> are required to guard against those things that are calculated to do
  the most evil. The little foxes spoil the vines<span class="footRef">21</span>&mdash;little evils do the most injury to the Church. If you
  have evil feelings,<span class="footRef">22</span> and speak of them to one another,<span class="footRef">23</span> it has a tendency to do mischief. These
  things</p>
